			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p25">4.0 Observations - Feral (Bear)</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=25#p25"><img src="./styles/thedruidsgrove/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">Sildan</a></strong> &raquo; Sun Oct 17, 2010 2:46 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Seems like the change to less bonus but higher base armor ratings on gear is nearly a wash. In the end I still have approximately the same armor. The added cooldown on Swipe really makes tanking more than a couple mobs an increased challenge. My understanding is that this is a tank wide change to decrease AE agro control. I think this is going to essentially transfer the responsibility to the other classes to control their agro. Seems like if they just relax a few more seconds and let me get that extra Swipe and Demo Roar out then I am able to maintain control ( Based on ICC trash pulls ). Rage generation is now a big problem for me. I used to never run low on rage, now I am constantly Rage Challenged. This forces a large decrease in my Maul usage.<br /><br />What are your findings?</div>

			

		</div>

		
